            "chars": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>LD.VI.R8</em></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Now Ladies &ndash; Now Darlings</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-203be841-7fff-33ad-4bd2-f9c2d5974e10\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These phrases summarize the repeated refrains within the theatre of &ldquo;ladies&rdquo; and &ldquo;darlings&rdquo;: &ldquo;[A] monotonous boy in a Scotch cap put his head round a beam on the left, and said, &ldquo;&lsquo;Now, ladies!&rsquo; said the boy in the Scotch cap. &lsquo;Now, darlings!&rsquo; said the gentleman with the black hair&rdquo; (LD 228).&nbsp;</p>"
